Accessibility test digest

Synopsis

Page: Instacart cart

URL: https://www.instacart.com/store/cvs/storefront

Score: 689

Tested by: Testaro, script instacartcart

Scored by: Testilo, procedure sp10c

Digested by: Testilo, procedure dp10c

Introduction

The instacartcart accessibility testing script was executed by Testaro on the Instacart cart web page arrived at in a transaction that began at https://www.instacart.com/store/cvs/storefront, on 2022/06/15. The procedure performed custom tests defined by Testaro and tests belonging to packages created by others. Testaro produced a report enumerating the test results.

Testilo used its sp10c scoring procedure to compute partial and total scores for the page. The total score is 689 (where 0 is the best possible score). The scored report is appended below.

Finally, Testilo used procedure dp10c to produce this digest, explaining how sp10c computed the scores.

Disclaimer: Even though there are widely accepted accessibility standards, there is still no unanimity about how to define, test for, and quantify accessibility. The failures reported below merit investigation as potential opportunities for improved accessibility. But you may conclude that some of the failures do not actually harm accessibility, and some substantial accessibility faults can escape detection by any of these tests. Likewise, you may not agree with weightings and formulas of scoring procedure sp10b, or even question whether it is appropriate to assign accessibility scores to a web page. This digest describes only one interpretation of the page’s accessibility.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 203. This is based on the amount of browser logging during the tests. Browsers usually log messages only when pages contain erroneous code.

log: Score 100. This is based on tests that the page did not allow to be run. That impedes accessibility progress and risks interfering with tools that users with disabilities need.

log: Score 17. This is based on issues reported by unclassified tests. Details are in the report.

Classified issues

The classified issues reported by tests are summarized below.

focusIndication: Score 101. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 24 issues reported by package alfa, test r65 (Element in sequential focus order has visible focus)
  • 19 issues reported by package testaro, test focInd (Focused element displaying no or nostandard focus indicator)

tabFocusability: Score 51. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 15 issues reported by package testaro, test focAll (Discrepancy between elements that should be and that are Tab-focusable)

inconsistentStyles: Score 50. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 48 issues reported by package testaro, test styleDiff (Heading, link, and button style inconsistencies)

roleBad: Score 39. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 0 issues reported by package axe, test aria-allowed-role (ARIA role should be appropriate for the element)
  • 0 issues reported by package ibm, test v:aria_semantics_role (ARIA roles must be valid for the element to which they are assigned)
  • 11 issues reported by package testaro, test role (Nonexistent or implicit-overriding role)

focusableOperable: Score 30. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 8 issues reported by package testaro, test focOp (Operable elements that cannot be Tab-focused and vice versa)

hoverSurprise: Score 28. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 26 issues reported by package testaro, test hover (Content changes caused by hovering)

contrastAA: Score 26. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 2 issues reported by package alfa, test r69 (Text outside widget has minimum contrast)
  • 6 issues reported by package axe, test color-contrast (Elements must have sufficient color contrast)
  • 0 issues reported by package ibm, test v:IBMA_Color_Contrast_WCAG2AA (Contrast ratio of text with background must meet WCAG 2.1 AA)
  • 0 issues reported by package wave, test c:contrast (Very low contrast)

textBeyondLandmarks: Score 16. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 14 issues reported by package alfa, test r57 (Perceivable text content not included in any landmark)

linkUnderlines: Score 12. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 4 issues reported by package testaro, test linkUl (Non-underlined inline links)

contrastAAA: Score 7. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 5 issues reported by package alfa, test r66 (Text contrast less than AAA requires)
  • 0 issues reported by package tenon, test 95 (Element has insufficient color contrast (Level AAA))

dupID: Score 6. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 0 issues reported by package aatt, test e:F77 (Duplicate id attribute value)
  • 0 issues reported by package alfa, test r3 (Element has no unique ID)
  • 1 issues reported by package axe, test duplicate-id (ID attribute value must be unique)
  • 0 issues reported by package ibm, test RPT_Elem_UniqueId (Element id attribute values must be unique within a document)

visibleBulk: Score 3. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • 1 issues reported by package testaro, test bulk (Count of visible elements as a multiple of 300)
